      "cardId": "s4-4001",
      "type": "mcq",
      "question": {
        "en": "In Latin noun–adjective phrases, adjectives must agree with the noun in:"
      },
      "correctAnswer": "number, gender, and case",
      "options": [
        "tense only",
        "number only",
        "number, gender, and case",
        "person and mood"
      ],
      "explanation": {
        "en": "Grammatical concord: adjectives match nouns in number, gender, and case. (Exercise IV, p.19)"
      }
    },
    {
      "cardId": "s4-4002",
      "type": "mcq",
      "question": {
        "en": "A 2-noun medical phrase with the second noun in genitive usually corresponds to English:"
